# Live Sports UX Standards

- Keep the main Sports view focused on content; put dense controls in a filter sheet or disclosure areas.
- Preserve provider model semantics: home provider in settings, temporary provider as explicit override.
- Always show why ordering changed when possible (availability/live/favorite signals, window effects).
- Keep event cards scannable: matchup first, status/time second, network/availability third, actions last.
- Prefer icon actions for compact rows, but always pair with accessibility labels and tooltips/help text.
- Use local device time for start times; avoid raw feed timezone abbreviations in primary text.
- Keep empty and constrained states actionable (example: suggest wider window when only one league appears).

